body:
Antique Primitive Ladder Back Chair
Firm on price.
For it`s age this chair is in remarkable shape and
rare to find in this condition.
Need a home office chair or a chair for extra seating
when you have dinner quests? Grab this antique
gorgeous chair and put it to work.
This ladder back chair dates back to the early 1900`s.
It features a curved back with a woven rush seat.
The wood frame of this chair has been totally refinished
having been sanded smooth and a coat of sealer was applied
followed with several coats of polyurethane to withstand daily
wear and tear.
The back of this chair is extremely comfortable because
the three back slats are slightly curved to provide more comfort
with a hand woven rush cane seat.
When not in use at the table sit it in your home office,
so versatile.
I consider it to be in perfect vintage condition and ready
to add some vintage flair to your home.
Measurements:
Height: 34.00 inches
Width: 16.50 inches
Depth: 14.00 inches
Seat: 18.00 inches off of the floor
Email with any questions. Cash only.

I have this very unique Clock that i have had for years.
I have never seen a clock like this!
Their are no visible markings on the out side just designs.
On the bottom their is a wind up knob and two other knobs to set the time and speed
In side a glass case their is a globe that tells the time with a dial that points to the time on the globe,
and two fish, one that moves back and forth for the seconds, and one that moves for the minutes.
It measures 5 1/2`` tall and 3 1/2`` round
Like i said i have never seen a clock like this before! If you have please let me know.
I could be listing this for more or less than it`s worth but i have no reference to compare it to?
573-462-992 Ask for tim, or leave a message
